{
  "stem": "10698.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I can't say really spoiled brat, but I'm the youngest.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, and there's a saying in-- back home, for the youngest child, [NON-ENGLISH], if you ever heard that expression.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were so proud [LAUGHS] even though that I was not expected anymore.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had a very-- for the 16 years until the war broke out, I had the most marvelous life, the most comfortable life.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Devora [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Leia ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Franco ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I'll tell you what-- my, my father, God rest his soul, he used to call her [NON-ENGLISH], which was pet name, like.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But whenever we heard him say Devora [NON-ENGLISH], that meant he's angry about something.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Otherwise, it was [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Velishee ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My-- our mom was treated like a queen in the house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And even though we had a live-in maid-- I don't remember ever being one day without a, without a live-in maid.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yet, Momma always used to say, you shouldn't have to, but you should know how to, expecting that we will marry comfortable enough to, to have a maid again.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But my momma did the cooking and baking.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was famous for it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "School was that we used to bring-- the people used to bring-- when there was parents' meetings, everybody brought something, and it was sold to each other.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the money went for the poor children's milk or lunches.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I never went to school without one lunch-- always two because I sat in the same seat with a girl that was, had-- didn't have a father.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She was a half an orphan.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my mom made sure that came holidays, got donated also different things for the holidays.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She had six, but we were five alive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My oldest brother was Shimon.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My, the second one was [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Leepa Mandel ?].",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
